tanzaniapark.com/blogs/top-5-fastest-birds-in-the-world/)but this record is specifically for its hunting dive (stoop). [2](https://www.vedantu.com/general-knowledge/top-10-fastest-birds-in-the-world), [9](https://www.vedantu.com/general-knowledge/top-10-fastest-birds-in-the-world)In sustained, level flapping flight, swifts and other species often demonstrate higher efficiency and velocity.\n[7](https://www.vernonchalmers.photography/2026/05/top-10-fastest-birds-in-world.html), [10](https://www.vernonchalmers.photography/2026/05/top-10-fastest-birds-in-world.html)*   **Measurement Challenges:** Measuring bird speed is complex. [6](https://www.animalfunfacts.net/animal-records/birds/200-the-fastest-birds.html)Factors such as wind assistance, the method of measurement (radar vs. GPS), and whether the bird is migrating or hunting can lead to variations in reported data.\n[3](https://grokipedia.com/page/List_of_birds_by_flight_speed), [6](https://www.animalfunfacts.net/animal-records/birds/200-the-fastest-birds.html)*   **Evolutionary Purpose:** High speed in birds is usually an evolutionary adaptation for specific survival needs. [7](https://www.vernonchalmers.photography/2026/05/top-10-fastest-birds-in-world.html), [4](https://www.discoverwildlife.com/animal-facts/birds/fastest-birds-world)Raptors utilize gravity to strike prey with precision, [2](https://www.vedantu.com/general-knowledge/top-10-fastest-birds-in-the-world), [4](https://www.discoverwildlife.com/animal-facts/birds/fastest-birds-world)while swifts and other long-distance flyers have evolved aerodynamic shapes for high-speed sustained travel.[7](https://www.vernonchalmers.photography/2026/05/top-10-fastest-birds-in-world.html), [10](https://www.vernonchalmers.photography/2026/05/top-10-fastest-birds-in-world.html)"
